cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

The paper deals with 3D shape reconstruction from 2D observations, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of differentiable ray consistency and multi-view supervision suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves learning frameworks and empirical analysis, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of 3D shapes and objects suggests that the paper may also be categorized under graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO).
